An arrest has been made over the death of a man in a Glasgow flat.Police were called to reports of a disturbance in a flat in Benalder Street, Partick, at 8.50am yesterday and found 29-year-old Scott Gillies seriously injured.He was treated by paramedics but died at the scene.Officers described the death as &quot;suspicious&quot; and launched an investigation.A 23-year-old man has now been arrested in connection with the death.A report will be sent to the procurator fiscal and the man is due to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday.Police said a 25-year-old woman was also injured in the incident and is being treated at Glasgow's Western Infirmary.